INSERT INTO `djangocms_text_ckeditor_text` VALUES (4,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) is one of the four inaugural schools of ShanghaiTech University. SIST\'s mission is to cultivate, nurture, educate, and train future technology innovators, enterprise leaders, R&amp;D specialists, and entrepreneurs in information science and technology. The SIST integrates world-leading scientific research environment with life-enriching and transformative education experience for our students.<br>\n<br>\nThe Schools cutting-edge research activities are designed to address global and national strategic challenges and needs of information science and technology. The School promotes both basic and applied research of the highest level by recruiting world-class scholars and researchers with international reputation as faculty members to establish state-of-the-art core technology laboratories, by collaborating broadly and closely with world-leading universities, research institutions, and hi-tech companies, and by taking advantages of Yangtze Deltas vibrant eco-environment rich with academic talents, financial strength, hi-tech industrial base, and superb regional economic policies. SIST is committed to undertaking and support national key R&amp;D projects, with strong aspiration for scientific and technological breakthroughs. SIST has the clear objective of becoming a regional, national, and international development workhorse by directly contributing to global technological advances with creative ideas and disruptive innovations.<br>\n<br>\nThe School emphasizes the establishment of an innovative and personalized education system for our undergraduate and post-graduate students. Our curriculum centers on individual academic supervision in all educational processes and learning activities. We promote an innovative and modernized educational experience to keep pace with rapidly evolving R&amp;D areas of information science and technology. In doing so, SIST can provide personalized teaching and training programs for students of various interests, backgrounds, and needs. The School continues to deliver a cutting-edge curriculum that consists of practical/advanced courses, exchange programs and internship opportunities with world-leading universities, research institutions, and hi-tech companies. We also offer special joint degree programs with international partner universities. By integrating teaching (campus), research (laboratory), and practice (company), SIST is proud of its competitive graduates who exhibit balanced characteristics of vision, ethics, responsibility, leadership, creativity, and entrepreneurship.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Main Research Areas:</strong></h3>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>1) Electrical Engineering</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Analog and Digital Circuits, Power Electronics and Systems, Intelligent Machines &amp; Robotics.</li>\n <li>Signal Processing, Information Theory, Communications Networks, Control Theory and Systems.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>2) Computer Engineering</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Architecture, Compiler, Operating Systems, Software Engineering</li>\n  <li>Multi-core and Parallel Computing, Computer Networks, High Performance Computing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>3) Computer Science</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Computation Theory, Algorithms, Database</li>\n <li>Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Big Data and Cloud Computing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>4) Computing &amp; Mathematical Science</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Optimization, Numerical Analysis, Applied Statistics, Distributed and Parallel Computing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>5) Interdisciplinary Information Technology</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Bioinformatics, Bioengineering, &amp; Biomedical Engineering (with SLST).</li>\n  <li>Microelectronics, devices, &amp; optics (with SPST)</li>\n  <li>Sensor Networks and Cyber-Physical Systems (with SPST, SEM)</li>\n  <li>Renewable Energy Technology (with SPST)</li>\n  <li>Social Networks and Applications (with SEM)</li>\n  <li>Quantum Computing and Next Generation Computing (with SPST, SLST)</li>\n</ul>\n'),(10,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) at ShanghaiTech University will lead the charge inChina\'s higher education reform by becoming a top academic research institution that is home toworld-class research laboratories and faculty members. The School\'s Mission is to createa unique open and free academic environment that enables all researchers young and senior to achieve their fullacademic potentials. The School will serve as the cradle that trains future scientists, engineers, entrepreneurs, and industrial leaders in information sciences and technologies to play key roles in the ongoing economic transformation of China and the world. </p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img id=\"plugin_obj_18\" title=\"Picture - sist-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(12,'<p>Welcome to the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, a place full of academic passion and research expertise.</p>\n\n<p>As you surf through our website, I believe that you will find a team of world-class faculty members, a group of creative and hardworking students, and many research areas that are well connected with domestic and international IT fields. Please join us in witnessing how ShanghaiTech is to become one of the best research institutes in the world.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img id=\"plugin_obj_22\" title=\"Picture - dean.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(14,'<p><strong>Faculty Search Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a>,<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=329\"><u>Zhi Ding</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Faculty candidate screening, interview, and recommendation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Staff Search Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Academic and administrative personnel search and recruiting.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Academic Affairs (SAA) Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Graduate and Undergraduate Programs.</li>\n <li>Degree requirements and petitions.</li>\n <li>Academic conduct regulations.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Curriculum and Teaching Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=132\"><u>Hao Chen</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Course planning and new course approval.</li>\n <li>Undergraduate student advising and mentor program.</li>\n <li>Graduate student advising.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Graduate Recruitment and Admissions (GRA) Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=8\"><u>Pingqiang Zhou</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Graduate admission policies, procedures, and decisions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>SAcademic Seminar (SAS) Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=6\"><u>Ziyu Shao</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Organizing and hosting SIST seminars and distinguished lectures.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Public Relation and Collaboration Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=209\"><u>Youyi Zheng</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>International and industrial collaboration.</li>\n  <li>SIST webpage management, newsletters Production.</li>\n <li>Public relation and societal outreach.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Research Developing and Planning Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Research developing and planning.</li>\n  <li>Lab equipment planning and budget.</li>\n <li>Research and lab management.</li>\n</ul>\n'),(28,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) at ShanghaiTech University will lead the charge inChina\'s higher education reform by becoming a top academic research institution that is home toworld-class research laboratories and faculty members. The School\'s Mission is to createa unique open and free academic environment that enables all researchers young and senior to achieve their fullacademic potentials. The School will serve as the cradle that trains future scientists, engineers, entrepreneurs, and industrial leaders in information sciences and technologies to play key roles in the ongoing economic transformation of China and the world.</p>\n'),(30,'<p>School of Information Science and Technology</p>\n'),(31,'<p>School of Information Science and Technology</p>\n'),(32,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(33,'<p>School of Information Science and Technology<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n</p>\n'),(35,'<p>SIST</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_38\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - sist-1_nb3zhrv.jpg\"></p>\n'),(43,'<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_44\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - dean_tLoNDas.jpg\"></p>\n'),(45,'<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=302\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=11\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=6\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=5\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=93\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong>Newsletter</p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u></u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong></strong></p>\n'),(50,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(52,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(54,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(65,'<p>1029Robert J. Birgeneau/HTCTsu-Jae King Liu,Scott BiddyDavid Jeu<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_66\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_67\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-2.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_68\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-1.jpg\"></p>\n'),(73,'<p>October 29, 2012: Today, ShanghaiTech and the University of California, Berkeley signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to launch a collaboration in education, culture, and scientific research over the next five years. The signing ceremony was held at Shanghai Pudong Science and Technology Park of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS). Dr. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, and Dr. Robert J. Birgeneau, Chancellor of the University of California, Berkeley, signed the MoU. Dr. Renchang Hua, Chief Commander of Pudong Science and Technology Park, Dr. Jie Yin, Deputy Director of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, Ms. Cher Wang, Chairperson of VIA/HTC Group, Dr. Zihe Rao, Academician of CAS, Dr. Songlin Feng, President of the Shanghai Advanced Research Institute, CAS (SARI) and Dr. Jinkang Gong, Principal of International Affairs of ShanghaiTech University attended the ceremony along with delegates from UC Berkeley including Dr. Tsu-Jae King Liu, Electrical Engineering Division Chair and Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences Associate Chair, College of Engineering, Mr. Scott Biddy, Vice Chancellor for University Relations, Mr. David Jeu, Assistant Vice Chancellor for International Relations, as well as other staff with the delegation.<br>\n<br>\nShanghaiTech and UC Berkeley have agreed to be in partnership in education, culture and scientific research over the next five years. As a start to the education collaboration program, faculty in the Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences in the UC Berkeley College of Engineering, will share some of their core course instruction resources and instructional materials and references with a selection of courseware being developed for online format. For each course, ShanghaiTech University will send faculty members to UC Berkeley to learn their counterpart faculty members pedagogical and and research methodology.<br>\n<br>\nThe MoU signed between ShanghaiTech University and UC Berkeley represents a significant move for ShanghaiTech in promoting high-level international collaboration to boost disciplinary development and deepen its educational vision of sharing and openness in order to be a globally recognized research university.<br>\n<br>\nThe University of California, Berkeley serves as a worlds premier public research university. It is recognized as a major source of future talent. With the mission of teaching, research, and public service, UC Berkeley has earned its top ranking and global reputation through its time-honored history and outstanding academic achievements.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_74\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945_87RSPiY.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_75\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-2_F12jQL3.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_76\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-1_uzBAveM.jpg\"></p>\n'),(81,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(83,'<p align=\"left\">ShanghaiTech University recently hosted a highly successful 2012 Frontiers of Information Science and Technology (FIST-2012) Workshop. FIST-2012 took place from December 9-13, 2012 at Parkyard Hotel, Zhangjiang Hi-tech Park, Pudong New Area, Shanghai. This high-level international workshop is initiated and organized by the School of Information Science and Technology. FIST-2012 workshop is one of a series of technical events during the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University.<br>\n<br>\nFIST-2012 invited over 60 major speakers from around the world, a large number of which are world-class senior researchers, professors and industrial experts. Focusing on the future development of scientific research and education in information science and technology, these distinguished speakers presented their recent exciting research findings, discussed important technological progresses, and articulated their visions on future research directions. More than 200 workshop participants took part in this unprecedented meeting of world class IT experts, covering a wide spectrum of frontier topics from big data, computer vision, to sub-millimeter wave imaging. FIST-2012 also invited Professor David Tse of UC Berkeley and IBMs Dr. David Carmel to deliver two plenary lectures titled The Science of Information: from Communications to DNA Sequencing and IBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge, respectively. The plenary lectures stimulated a high level of attention and exciting discussions among workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p align=\"left\"><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1_ud3iifC.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_94\"></p>\n\n<p>Dr. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, delivered the opening lecture titled Urbanization, Industrialization, and Informationization during the opening ceremony. Following the progress and modernization of society through, urbanization, industrialization, and the recent informationization, Dr. Jiang delineated the general development trend of society through information revolution and globalization. He further emphasized the necessity, importance, and urgency for China and Chinas education system to break through traps and stagnation experienced earlier by nations in similar stage of development and modernization. Dr. Jiang introduced the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University as the governments response and commitment to confront these difficult challenges.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2_N3urfAw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_95\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Jie Yin, Deputy Director of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, presented the founding principles, the planning, and the current progress of ShanghaiTech University in his major speech on behalf of the ShanghaiTech University Steering Committee.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3_rRfZdVX.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_96\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Zhi Ding of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) served as the chair of the workshop and the opening ceremony. On behalf of Dean Cher Wang and the SIST team, he articulated the founding principles and future plan of SIST in his talk. Prof. Ding also presented the preparation and progress of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) to the workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p>Among the distinguished guests at the workshop are Renchang Hua, Vice President of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, Cher Wang, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean of SIST, Zhihe Rao, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean from School of Life Science and Technology, Yang Yang, Vice Dean of SIST, Hong Li, Vice Dean from School of Entrepreneurship and Management as well as Wenchi Chen, CEO of ViaTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4_ySnnSEw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_97\"></p>\n'),(84,'<p>2012129-132012FIST-2012<br>\n<br>\n60 61200<br>\n<br>\n115Future Data Technologies and Intelligent Systems,Information Theory and Foundations for future Communication and Energy Systems,Embedded Systems and Low Energy Electronics,Interdisciplinary TechnologiesNext Generation Computing David Tse IBM David Carmel The Science of Information: from Communication to DNA SequencingIBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_85\"></p>\n\n<p>Urbanization, Industrialization &amp; Informationization</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_86\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_87\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_88\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n'),(103,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(104,'<p>On December 28th, ShanghaiTech University laid its foundation in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), which marks substantial progress has been made in the preparatory work for establishing the university.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1_TP3DDqk.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_149\"></p>\n\n<p>Ms. Yicui YinDeputy Secretary of the Shanghai CPC Committee, Prof. Erwei Shi, Vice President of CAS, Prof. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, along with Mr. Lin Xu, Secretary of Pudong New District CPC Committee, Mr. Xuebing Zhang and Mr. Xiaoming Shen, Vice Mayors of Shanghai Municipal Government, visited the laboratories of ShanghaiTech University and investigated the campus master plan.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2_Jyy3iPK.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_150\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3_Ej0Yt4b.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_151\"></p>\n\n<p>Around 200 professors of ShanghaiTech University, leaders from departments of Shanghai Municipal Government and Pudong New Area Government, representatives from other universities in Shanghai, principals of CAS Shanghai Branch and institutes as well as delegates from partners involved in campus design and construction witnessed the launch of campus construction project altogether.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4_JnheOOm.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_152\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Bird\'s View</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5_WgpppZb.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_153\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Library</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6_e43iOqe.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_154\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Teaching Block</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7_WiW6dLY.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_155\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Arts and Venue Street</p>\n\n<p>Located at the center of Zhangjiang high-tech industrial development zone, ShanghaiTech integrates with Shanghai Advanced Research Institute (SARI) in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science and Technology Park, which covers approximately one square kilometer. At the established Multidisciplinary Frontier Research Base in Pudong S&amp;T Park of CAS, room has been reserved for universitys laboratories, classrooms and offices. The laboratories have been initiated in advance.</p>\n'),(105,'<p>1228</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_134\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_135\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_136\"></p>\n\n<p>200</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_137\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_138\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_139\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_140\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p>1265</p>\n'),(111,'<p>On May 11th, the ceremony marking the beginning of construction of ShanghaiTech University was held in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1_9KewrJE.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_115\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2_CGoidJ1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_116\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3_xDiEWpn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_117\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4_K7R5wn1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_118\"></p>\n'),(112,'<p>2013511</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_124\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_125\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_126\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_127\"></p>\n'),(164,'<p>On the morning of July 8th, ShanghaiTech 2013 summer camp for undergraduates formally kicked off in YueYang Road campus with 212 participants from 123 universities all over the country. Professor Mianheng Jiang, Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and President of Shanghai Branch, Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), handed the Camp flag over to the student representative on behalf of ShanghaiTech and initiated the camp. Professor Jie Yin, Vice Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Deputy Director of Shanghai Education Commission, Professor Jinkang Gong, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, as well as leaders of ShanghaiTech schools and institutes attended the opening ceremony.<br>\n<br>\nProfessor Mianheng Jiang delivered a speech named Realizing China Dream through Innovation and Entrepreneurship. He elaborated on the founding idea and mission of ShanghaiTech combined with national development strategy and social needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_uW6jad6.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_165\"></p>\n\n<p>Professor Jie Yin outlined the preparation progress of ShanghaiTech University. ShanghaiTech University is characterized as a small-scale, high-level research university. It will tightly integrate education with innovative research and entrepreneurship to meet national and local development needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_UuzZRDW.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_166\"><br>\nProfessor Jinkang Gong explained in detail the training program of ShanghaiTech for graduate students, which ensures the implementation of the founding idea and the mission of ShanghaiTech.<br>\n<img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_psrEDRF.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_167\"><br>\nIn the end of the ceremony, an overview of School of Physical Science and Technology (SPST), School of Information Science and Technology (SIST), School of Life Science and Technology (SLST), as well as School of Entrepreneurship and Management (SEM) was presented.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4_eJbJPnn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_168\"></p>\n\n<p>This was the 2nd Summer Camp held by ShanghaiTech University. Three schools respectively arranged a variety of activities for students according to their different subject characteristics. Participants of SPST will enter into different institutes of CAS Shanghai Branch, getting involved in group research, and students of SIST will compete in groups learning how to solve practical problems with classroom knowledge, while students of SLST will have the chance to join seminars where excellent reports will be presented by academicians and renowned scholars.</p>\n'),(174,'<p>782013  123212  </p>\n\n<p>+</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_Qf1Adfm.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_175\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_pY2mH8R.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_176\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_NnkqS10.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_177\"></p>\n\n<p>iHuman</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_178\"></p>\n\n<p>   </p>\n'),(184,'<p>89111022154 </p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_185\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_186\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_187\"></p>\n\n<p>   </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-4.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_188\"></p>\n'),(194,'<p>93296 12 </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_195\"></p>\n\n<p>   </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_196\"></p>\n\n<p>  3D </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_197\"></p>\n\n<p>HyperloopElon Musk </p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_198\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_199\"></p>\n\n<p>iHumanRaymond C. Stevens </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_200\"></p>\n\n<p>  </p>\n\n<p>2013</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_201\"></p>\n'),(210,'<p>ShanghaiTechs first batch of 296 graduate students started their first day of 2013 semester on September 3rd. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1_SsCQCix.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_211\"></p>\n\n<p>The ceremony was organized in a novel and human-oriented format to match this brand new university. In front of the slideshow of the self-introduction of each student, the dean of each school announced the names of their students one by one. Madam Tiehui Weng, Deputy Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and Vice Mayor of Shanghai, granted each of the 3 student representatives an experiment record notebook and a crystal key as symbols of fact-finding spirit and pursuit of knowledge. What impressed the participants most was the exalting speech from Prof.Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2_yUa0O3U.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_212\"><br>\nCentering around Jinping Xis Chinese Dream, Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3_M242EmH.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_213\"></p>\n\n<p>Jiang encouraged the students to learn from Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who made Space X and Tesla the electrical car, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop the super high-speed train), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Jiang also mentioned the Chinese mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the bounded gaps conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4_wPNOKe3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_214\"></p>\n\n<p>As professor representatives, Xi Wang(Academician, Director of Shanghai Institute of Microsystem and Information Technology) and Raymond Stevens (Director of iHuman Institute of ShanghaiTech) reflected on their academic experience, expressed their excitement to join ShanghaiTech and encouraged the students to seize the day.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5_P6ts1Zd.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_215\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6_Tke5VH9.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_216\"></p>\n\n<p>Mingchao Jiang, a student from School of Physical Science and Technology, gave the speech on behalf of the new students and talked about his understanding on innovation and human-centeredness.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7_dtF30kv.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_217\"></p>\n\n<p>At the end of the ceremony,Mianheng Jiang officially announced the opening of the semester. After the ceremony students had an interaction session with professors.</p>\n'),(226,'<p><span><span style=\"\"><span>296 young graduate students began their exciting ShanghaiTech career on September 3</span><sup><span>rd</span></sup><span>, 2013. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>The ceremony adopted non-traditional format to match this brand new university. Accompanied by slideshows, each school introduced their students one by one. Vice Major Tiehui Weng, Deputy Chief of the ShanghaiTech Preparation Work-Group, presented a lab notebook and a crystal key as symbols of truth searching spirit and pursuit of knowledge. As a highlight of the event, participants were treated by an exalting speech from Prof. Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Centering around the theme of Chinese Dream, Dr. Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Dr. Jiang encouraged the students to learn from individuals like Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who started Space X and Tesla, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Dr. Jiang also mentioned the example of a previously obscure mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the bounded gaps conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_227\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\"></span></span></p>\n'),(230,'<p>Two officers of the National Natural Science Foundation fo China, Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on September 28th.</p>\n\n<p>They received warm welcome by SIST faculty professors. Prof. Zhi Ding, Prof. Shuguang Cui and Prof. Pingqiang Zhou met Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, introduced our university and school, and had a constructive talk with them.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532_boPUFVB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_231\"></p>\n'),(234,'<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_235\"></p>\n\n<p>928</p>\n'),(238,'<p>1010Young Idea AwardYoung Idea Award</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_263\"></p>\n\n<p>2083</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_247\"></p>\n'),(239,'<p><span><span><span>A Contest named <em>Young Idea Award </em>was successfully held on November 10</span><sup><span>th</span></sup><span>, which was sponsored by SIST and received kind support from the office of Financial Services and the School of Entrepreneurship and Management at ShanghaiTech.<em> Young Idea Award </em>was designed for encouraging graduate students who have different and innovative understanding on scientific research or entrepreneurship. All the students from ShanghaiTech University were welcomed to join in the contest.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_259\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\"></p>\n\n<p><span>Over 20 students in eight teams took part in the contest. The topic named Creative Campus, which was designed by Yuying Bao, Xiangyu Jia, Ziran Xing from SIST, finally won the first prize.</span></p>\n\n<p><span><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_243\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\"></span></p>\n'),(250,'<p>102930</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_251\"></p>\n'),(254,'<p><span><span>On behalf of the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, </span><span><span>Prof. Zhi Ding and Prof. Shuguang Cui took part in</span></span><span><span> the Future (5G) ICT Summit &amp; 5G Mobile and Communication Technologies Workshop, which was Hosted by FuTURE FORUM, co-organized by METIS Project and China Mobile and held in Beijing during Oct 29th</span><span>  Oct 30th</span><span>. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5_fZwIZWL.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_255\"></p>\n'),(267,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(268,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(277,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(287,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(376,'<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_378\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_379\"></p>\n\n<p>118Stephen Boyd100Stephen BoydStephen Boyd</p>\n'),(377,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(384,'<p>Prof. Stephen Boyd, Samsung Professor of Engineering, and a Professor of Electrical Engineering at Stanford University, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on November 8<sup>th</sup>and presented an exciting seminar on Convex Optimization: From Real-Time Embedded to Large-Scale Distributed. Over 100 graduated students and faculty members from ShanghaiTech, Southeast University and Shanghai University, enjoyed the high-quality seminar, which stimulated many productive discussions.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_385\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Boydstalk focused on two extremes: real-time embedded convex optimization, and distributed convex optimization. For the first one, code generation can be used to generate extremely efficient and reliable solvers for small problems, which can execute in milliseconds or microseconds, and are ideal for embedding in real-time systems. At the other extreme, Prof. Boyed described methods for large-scale distributed optimization, which coordinate many solvers to solve large problems. Prof. Boyds talk is open, humorous, informative, and inspiring. The large crowd at the seminar includes faculty members from as for as Nanjing. In addition, the Audience was also treated with someaspiring insightsonhow to conduct high-quality research and how to become a real scholar.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" style=\"line-height: 1.6;\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_386\"></p>\n'),(390,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(479,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(492,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(523,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(525,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(529,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(538,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(548,'<p><img title=\"Picture - Examining the Landscape and Impact of Android Application Plagiarism.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_549\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(563,'<p><img title=\"Picture - A Brief Introduction to IC Design and EDA.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_573\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(571,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(643,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(647,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(651,'<p><img title=\"Picture - Classifying Computational Couning Problems.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_653\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(664,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(668,'<p><img title=\"Picture - Enlightenment from the development of MEMS.jpg