 of the Working Group of ShanghaiTech.<br>\n<em><strong>Ding Zhongli</strong></em>, Vice President of Chinese Academy of Sciences; Director of the Education Committee of CAS.<br>\n<em><strong>Fu Chengyu</strong></em><strong>,</strong>Chairman of China Petroleum &amp; Chemical Corporation.<br>\n<em><strong>Jiang Mianheng</strong></em><strong>,</strong>President of Chinese Academy of Sciences Shanghai Branch; Chairman of the Executive Committee of Shanghaitech.<br>\n<em><strong>Zhu Zhiyuan</strong></em><strong>,</strong>Executive Vice President of Chinese Academy of Sciences Shanghai Branch.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting was chaired by Xu Kuangdi.</p>\n\n<p>According to the By Laws of ShanghaiTech University approved by both CAS and Shanghai Municipality, the University Board of Trustees is the decision-making body of ShanghaiTech. It is composed of representatives from Shanghai Municipality, CAS, the university as well as expert from the industry. Its responsibilities include compiling and revising the By Laws, drafting the development strategy and plan; nominating the university President, appointing the administrative heads based on the President\'s nomination, reviewing the annual report, budget and final account, deciding the key issues of the university and etc,.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting reviewed the vision and goals of the university, the current status of teaching, research, recruitment, the campus construction and annual report 2014. The meeting approved the University Board of Trustees Rules of Procedure, key position appointment, as well as the final accounts of 2013 and budget for 2014.</p>\n\n<p>The University Board of Trustees pointed out that ShanghaiTech University has made considerable progress by reforming the university structure, management, nurturing of talents, human resource system and allocation of funding and has actively explored the deep integration of education, research and innovation. The members are confident that under the support of Ministry of Education, Shanghai Municipality, and the hard work of the all faculty and staff, ShanghaiTech will make new achievements in 2014.<img title=\"Picture - 201403061346428421_z38VaAJ.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1243\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1251,'<p>20143</p>\n\n<p>1995199720002000200620062011200920141999ICCVDavid Marr2004NSFCAREER Award2005Young Investigator Award2011Gold Star Award2013IEEE Fellow2007-2011IEEE Trans. on Pattern Analysis and Machine IntelligenceIEEE Trans. on Information TheoryInternational Journal of Computer VisionIMA Journal on Information and InferenceSIAM Journal on Imaging SciencesICCV</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201405161418534052.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1252\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1255,'<p>Dr. Yi Ma, a famous scholar in computer vision, joined in the School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech University as a full-time professor who would lead the study of computer vision in March, 2014.</p>\n\n<p>Yi Ma received Bachelors degree in Automation and Applied Mathematics from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China, in 1995. He received a Master degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences (EECS) in 1997, a second Master degree in Mathematics in 2000, and the Ph.D. degree in EECS in 2000, all from the University of California at Berkeley. He served as associated professor from 2000 to 2006 and vice professor from 2006 to 2011 of the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. From 2009 to 2014, he served as research manager for the Visual Computing Group at Microsoft Research Asia, Beijing, China. His PhD research won the David Marr Best Paper Award at the International Conference on Computer Vision (ICCV) in 1999. He was the recipient of the Faculty Early Career Development (CAREER) Award from the National Science Foundation (NSF) in 2004. He was also the recipient of the Young Investigator Program (YIP) Award from the Office of Naval Research (ONR) in 2005. He received the Gold Star Award from Microsoft Corporate in 2009. He has served as an associate editor of the IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence (TPAMI) from 2007 to 2011. He became a Fellow of IEEE in 2013. He has served as an associate editor of the IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence (TPAMI). He currently serves as the associate editors for the IEEE Transactions on Information Theory, the International Journal of Computer Vision (IJCV), the IMA Journal on Information and Inference, and the SIAM Journal on Imaging Sciences. He also served as the Area Chair, the Program Chair and the General Chair for ICCV and was invited to present reports in many international conferences.</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201405161418534052_S31shdt.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1256\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1259,'<p><img title=\"Picture - 201408191139291671.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1260\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p>(Thomas Reuters)20146(Highly Cited Researchers 2014http://highlycited.com)Web of Science1%212002-20123215The worlds most influential scientific minds.</p>\n\n<p>Dr. Cui19972000McMaster2005Texas A&amp;MDr. Cui)Dr. CuiIEEE2012,(IEEE TSP, TWC, TVT, CL)IEEE(WTC)IEEESPCOMDr. Cui2013IEEE Fellow8IEEE2014IEEE Transactions on Big DataSteering Committee</p>\n'),(1263,'<p>20149587,99</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1264\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1267,'<p>The faculty and staff of SIST joyfully welcome our new students coming in 2014, which include the first batch of undergraduate students and second batch of graduate students. Through substantial activities in the orientation, students got to know more about ShanghaiTech and strengthened their confidence towards future study and living here. The graduate courses have started since September 9. Undergraduate freshmen are going to set out for their long expected college education very soon after finishing their military training.</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974_c84HgXy.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1268\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1271,'<p></p>\n'),(1273,'<p>Prof. Jinyi Yu, Associate Professor at the University of Delaware, and Prof. Xin Li, Associate Professor at Carnegie Mellon University have joined the SIST as visiting professors.</p>\n'),(1275,'<p>20147Soeren SchwertfegerBoris Houska2015</p>\n'),(1277,'<p>The professors who have joined the SIST since July 2014 includes: Dr. Yanling Geng, Xiaojun Yuan, Shenghua Gao, Soeren Schwertfeger, Haoyu Wang, and Boris Houska as Assistant Professors, and Xiliang Luo as Associate Professor. In addition, 6 new colleagues include Dr. Xiaopei Liu, Dr. Jie Lu, Dr. Ziyang Meng, Dr. Xiong Wang, Dr. Liangfeng Zhang, Dr. Youyi Zheng will report on duty later in 2015.</p>\n'),(1279,'<p>2015122</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201501310004245165.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1280\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201501310004506755.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1281\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201501310005041729.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1282\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1287,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) has held their first retreat meeting in the Puxi campus at Jan. 22, 2015. All presidents of ShanghaiTech including President Mianheng Jiang, and some colleagues in other functional offices has also attended this meeting. In the meeting, Prof. Zhi Ding, the executive dean reviewed the faculty recruitment and development since establishing and summarized the guiding comments from the international advisory board. After that, the chairs of Academic Committee, Curriculum Committee, Graduate Admission Committee, Seminar Committee, and Public Relation Committee reported their achievements in 2014, introduced their drafted by-laws, and discussed their future plan. After the reports, the faculty members of SIST make an extensive communication with the university leaders regarding different issues about the school development; they have also made a brainstorm about their future roadmap.</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201501310004245165_hgmDMnB.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1288\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201501310004506755_syJmdXe.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1289\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201501310005041729_ZwroWNi.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1290\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1295,'<p>2015</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201502031733531115.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1296\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1299,'<p>Supported by the Berkeley-ShanghaiTech-Exchange (BeSTEC) Program, the first delegation of SIST@ShanghaiTech, consisting of Professor Pingqiang Zhou, Professor Shenghua Gao, and Mr. Kai Liao (2nd year graduate student), has started their Berkeley time from the last week of Jan. 2015.</p>\n\n<p>According to the program, professors and students of SIST can attend part of the Berkeley courses, which would later be offered to SIST students. This program will also help the junior faculty members at ShanghaiTech to build research connections with the faculty at Berkeley.</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201502031733531115_7F2rgXp.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1300\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1303,'<p>DAC (Design Automation Conference) 2015A Statistical Methodology for Noise Sensor Placement and Full-Chip Voltage Map Generation</p>\n\n<p>DACDAC6</p>\n'),(1305,'<p>SIST student Xiaochen Lius paper was accepted by Design Automation Conference (DAC) 2015. His paper is titled A Statistical Methodology for Noise Sensor Placement and Full-Chip Voltage Map Generation. Xiaochens advisor is Prof. Pingqiang Zhou.</p>\n\n<p>DAC is the premier conference for the design and automation of electronic systems. DAC 2015 will be held in San Francisco in June 2015.</p>\n'),(1307,'<p>2015420Leonidas GuibasNetworks of Shapes and Images</p>\n\n<p>Leonidas GuibasGuibasACM FellowIEEE Fellow, ACM Allen NewellVoronoi-DelaunayEMDKineticKDSMetropolis light transportheat-kernel signaturesfunctional maps</p>\n\n<p>GuibasGuibas</p>\n\n<p>Leonidas Guibas </p>\n\n<p> Leonidas Guibas 1976Donald KnuthXerox PARCDECDEC SRC1984John HershbergerJack SnoeyinkJorge Stolfi,  David SalesinEric Veach Niloy Mitra</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201504232315256998.JPG\" id=\"plugin_obj_1308\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1311,'<p>On April 20, 2015, Leonidas Guibas, professor of computer science at Stanford University, gave a talk named Networks of Shapes and Images to ShanghaiTech faculty and students.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Yi Ma, executive dean of School of Information Science and Technology (SIST), introduced the speakers academic career. As an ACM Fellow, an IEEE Fellow and winner of the ACM Allen Newell Award, Prof. Guibas is a well-known master in computer graphics. Some of his well-known accomplishments include the analysis of double hashing, red-black trees, the quad-edge data structure, Voronoi-Delaunay algorithms, the Earth Movers distance, Kinetic Data Structures (KDS), Metropolis light transport, heat-kernel signatures and functional maps.</p>\n\n<p>Prof. Guibas pointed out that, across science, engineering, medicine and business we faced a deluge of data coming from sensors, simulations or activities of individuals on the internet, and the data often contain geometric and/or visual characters. Furthermore, the geometric data sets we collected were frequently highly correlated, reflecting information about the same or similar entities, or echoing semantically important repetitions/symmetries or hierarchical structures common to both man-made and natural objects. He described general mathematical and computational tools for the construction, analysis and exploitation of such relational networks. By creating societies of data sets and their associations in a globally consistent way, we enabled a certain joint understanding of the data that provided the powers of abstraction, analogy, compression, error correction and summarization. Faculty and students were greatly attracted to the intriguing images Prof. Guibas showed during the talk, and had extensive discussion with him afterwards.</p>\n\n<p>Bio:</p>\n\n<p>Leonidas Guibas obtained his Ph.D. from Stanford in 1976, under the supervision of Donald Knuth. His subsequent employers include Xerox PARC, MIT, and DEC/SRC. He has been at Stanford since 1984 as Professor of Computer Science. He has produced several Ph.D. students who are well-known in computational geometry, such as John Hershberger, Jack Snoeyink and Jorge Stolfi, or in computer graphics, such as David Salesin, Eric Veach and Niloy Mitra.</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201504232315256998_OMLDqoo.JPG\" id=\"plugin_obj_1312\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1315,'<p>2015/()2.5MW / 4MW</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201505200733119750.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1317\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1320,'<p><i>Renewable Energy System</i>is a new graduate course offered in the fall semester of 2015. As a supplement to this course, the school has organized a field trip to a local sino-foreign wind power company, Shanghai Electric Wind Energy Co. Ltd / Siemens Wind Power Turbines (Shanghai) Co., Ltd. Thanks to the guidance of Yi Zhang, an engineer of the company, the visitors have listened to the state of the art of wind power industry in China, as well as the history of the company. After the introduction, they were guided to visit the assembly workshop of 2.5 MW / 4 MW wind turbines. Finally, they have a close look at the testing wind farm on the shore of East China Sea. The field trip has offered the students an immediate and memorable impression on renewable energy system and local wind power industry.</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201505200733119750_1PUK7EL.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1321\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1324,'<p>5263D</p>\n\n<p>3D3D3D3D</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 20150609133045145.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1325\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201506091331003762.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1326\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201506091331137173.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1327\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1328,'<p>On May 26th, Deputy director of Shanghai Museum Dr. Hu Jiang and President Jiang Mianheng, accompanied by Professor Ma Yi, executive dean of SIST, visited the 3D Imaging Lab housed at SIST.</p>\n\n<p>Prof. Yu Jingyi demonstrated a novel 3D imaging system to the visitors and gave an in-depth presentation on its acquisition, data transmission and display modules. Of particular interest is the portable camera array that enables naked-eye 3D viewing. All visitors were impressed by the demonstration. After that, the two parties have further discussed potential collaborations on applying the 3D imaging system for a broad range of applications at Shanghai Museum. President Jiang Mianheng pointed out that, integrating research and real-life application is central to the mission of ShanghaiTech and SIST. He hopes that discussions today will lead to concrete collaboration between ShanghaiTech and Shanghai Museum in the near future.</p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 20150609133045145_qMff62E.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1329\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201506091331003762_2ZwmfSB.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1330\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n\n<p><img title=\"Picture - 201506091331137173_P1lWPJ6.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_1331\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(1387,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1389,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1396,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1405,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1409,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1421,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1442,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1444,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1445,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1447,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1448,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1449,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1450,'<p><strong>Name: </strong>Cher Wang<br>\n<strong>Title: </strong>Dean<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email: </strong><br>\n<strong>Office: </strong><br>\n<strong>Homepage: </strong></p>\n'),(1452,'<p>Cher Wang has established a number of successful IT-related businesses, including founding VIA Technologies, Inc. and co-founding HTC Corporation. She is currently Chairwoman of both companies, and holds leadership roles in numerous other enterprises and organizations.</p>\n\n<p>Cher is active in the international business community, participating as an Industry Partner at the World Economic Forum and as a member of the APEC Business Advisory Council (ABAC). In 2010, Cher co-founded the ABAC Womens Forum to identify capacity-building policy recommendations that enhance opportunities for women in business, and to hold outreach activities within APEC economies. Chers business achievements have been widely acclaimed in major international media.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to her business roles, Cher has always been devoted to giving back to the society with a keen focus on education. She fully embraces ShanghaiTechs vision of emphasizing the integration of education, research and innovation, in order to further nurture outstanding talents engaged in scientific discovery, break-through inventions, and entrepreneurships.</p>\n\n<p>Cher graduated from the University of California, Berkeley, and is a devout Christian. She is married with two children.</p>\n'),(1465,'<p><strong>Title: </strong><br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email: </strong><br>\n<strong>Office: </strong><br>\n<strong>Homepage: </strong></p>\n'),(1466,'<p>VIA Technologies, Inc.HTCTVB2009APECABAC</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>HTCHTC</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>2005  Business Week2005 Stars of Asia25 25 Leaders on the Forefront of ChangeInnovator</p>\n'),(1492,'<p>VIA Technologies, Inc.HTC</p>\n'),(1510,'<p>Cher Wang is the founding dean of the School of Information Science and Technology, as well as Chairwoman of VIA Technologies, Inc. and HTC Corporation. She also holds leadership roles in numerous other enterprises and organizations. Cher graduated from the University of California, Berkeley.</p>\n'),(1525,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(1527,'\n                    <p><strong>Title: </strong>Title here<br></p>\n                    <p><strong>PHD: </strong>PHD here<br></p>\n                    <p><strong>Tel: </strong>Tel here<br></p>\n                    <p><strong>Email: </strong>Email here<br></p>\n                    <p><strong>Office: </strong>Office here<br></p>\n                    <p><strong>Homepage: </strong>Homepage here<br></p>\n                    '),(1528,'<p>Enter your bref introduction. This content will show on list page.</p>'),(1529,'<div class=\"peppdo2\">\n<p><strong style=\"color: #AD2005;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">M</span>ain <span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">R</span>esponsibility</strong></p>\n\n<p>1.<br>\n2.<br>\n3.<br>\n4.<br>\n5.<br>\n6.<br>\n7.</p>\n\n<p><strong style=\"color: #AD2005;\"