, she was a post-doctoral research fellow with the Institute of Network Coding of The Chinese University of Hong Kong first and then with the ACCESS post-doctoral researcher at the ACCESS Linnaeus Centre of KTH Royal Institute of Technology. She has joined the School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech University since Aug. 2015.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Her main research interests are in the area of wireless communication and networking, with current focus on green wireless, distributed algorithm and protocol design, signal processing, and wireless network optimization and control. She has published over 20 peer-reviewed research papers in the leading journals and prestigious conferences in the related field.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTEDPUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Ying Jun (Angela) Zhang, and Jianwei Huang, Energy Efficient Transmissions in MIMO Cognitive Radio Networks, IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications (JSAC), vol. 31, no. 11, pp. 2420-2431, Nov. 2013.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, Effective Carrier Sensing in CSMA Networks under Cumulative Interference, IEEE Transactions on Mobile Computing, vol. 12, no. 4, pp. 748-760, Apr. 2013.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Hongseok Kim, Jianwei Huang, Soung Chang Liew, and Mung Chiang, Energy Conservation and Interference Mitigation: From Decoupling Property to Win-Win Strategy, IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 10, no. 11, pp. 3943-3955, Nov. 2011.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, Fast Algorithms for Joint Power Control and Scheduling in Wireless Networks, IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 9, no. 3, pp. 1186-1197, Mar. 2010.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, Power Controlled Scheduling with Consecutive Transmission Constraints: Complexity Analysis and Algorithm Design, in Proc