nded the ceremony along with delegates from UC Berkeley including Dr. Tsu-Jae King Liu, Electrical Engineering Division Chair and Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences Associate Chair, College of Engineering, Mr. Scott Biddy, Vice Chancellor for University Relations, Mr. David Jeu, Assistant Vice Chancellor for International Relations, as well as other staff with the delegation.<br>\n<br>\nShanghaiTech and UC Berkeley have agreed to be in partnership in education, culture and scientific research over the next five years. As a start to the education collaboration program, faculty in the Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences in the UC Berkeley College of Engineering, will share some of their core course instruction resources and instructional materials and references with a selection of courseware being developed for online format. For each course, ShanghaiTech University will send faculty members to UC Berkeley to learn their counterpart faculty members pedagogical and and research methodology.<br>\n<br>\nThe MoU signed between ShanghaiTech University and UC Berkeley represents a significant move for ShanghaiTech in promoting high-level international collaboration to boost disciplinary development and deepen its educational vision of sharing and openness in order to be a globally recognized research university.<br>\n<br>\nThe University of California, Berkeley serves as a worlds premier public research university. It is recognized as a major source of future talent. With the mission of teaching, research, and public service, UC Berkeley has earned its top ranking and global reputation through its time-honored history and outstanding academic achievements.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945_87RSPiY.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945_87RSPiY.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6623\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-2_F12jQL3.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-2_F12jQL3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6624\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-1_uzBAveM.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-1_uzBAveM.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6625\"></p>\n'),(6626,'<p>2012129-132012FIST-2012<br>\n<br>\n60 61200<br>\n<br>\n115Future Data Technologies and Intelligent Systems,Information Theory and Foundations for future Communication and Energy Systems,Embedded Systems and Low Energy Electronics,Interdisciplinary TechnologiesNext Generation Computing David Tse IBM David Carmel The Science of Information: from Communication to DNA SequencingIBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6627\"></p>\n\n<p>Urbanization, Industrialization &amp; Informationization</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-2.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6628\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-3.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6629\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121221-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6630\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n'),(6631,'<p align=\"left\">ShanghaiTech University recently hosted a highly successful 2012 Frontiers of Information Science and Technology (FIST-2012) Workshop. FIST-2012 took place from December 9-13, 2012 at Parkyard Hotel, Zhangjiang Hi-tech Park, Pudong New Area, Shanghai. This high-level international workshop is initiated and organized by the School of Information Science and Technology. FIST-2012 workshop is one of a series of technical events during the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University.<br>\n<br>\nFIST-2012 invited over 60 major speakers from around the world, a large number of which are world-class senior researchers, professors and industrial experts. Focusing on the future development of scientific research and education in information science and technology, these distinguished speakers presented their recent exciting research findings, discussed important technological progresses, and articulated their visions on future research directions. More than 200 workshop participants took part in this unprecedented meeting of world class IT experts, covering a wide spectrum of frontier topics from big data, computer vision, to sub-millimeter wave imaging. FIST-2012 also invited Professor David Tse of UC Berkeley and IBMs Dr. David Carmel to deliver two plenary lectures titled The Science of Information: from Communications to DNA Sequencing and IBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge, respectively. The plenary lectures stimulated a high level of attention and exciting discussions among workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p align=\"left\"><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-1_ud3iifC.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1_ud3iifC.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6632\"></p>\n\n<p>Dr. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, delivered the opening lecture titled Urbanization, Industrialization, and Informationization during the opening ceremony. Following the progress and modernization of society through, urbanization, industrialization, and the recent informationization, Dr. Jiang delineated the general development trend of society through information revolution and globalization. He further emphasized the necessity, importance, and urgency for China and Chinas education system to break through traps and stagnation experienced earlier by nations in similar stage of development and modernization. Dr. Jiang introduced the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University as the governments response and commitment to confront these difficult challenges.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-2_N3urfAw.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2_N3urfAw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6633\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Jie Yin, Deputy Director of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, presented the founding principles, the planning, and the current progress of ShanghaiTech University in his major speech on behalf of the ShanghaiTech University Steering Committee.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-3_rRfZdVX.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3_rRfZdVX.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6634\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Zhi Ding of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) served as the chair of the workshop and the opening ceremony. On behalf of Dean Cher Wang and the SIST team, he articulated the founding principles and future plan of SIST in his talk. Prof. Ding also presented the preparation and progress of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) to the workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p>Among the distinguished guests at the workshop are Renchang Hua, Vice President of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, Cher Wang, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean of SIST, Zhihe Rao, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean from School of Life Science and Technology, Yang Yang, Vice Dean of SIST, Hong Li, Vice Dean from School of Entrepreneurship and Management as well as Wenchi Chen, CEO of ViaTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121221-4_ySnnSEw.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4_ySnnSEw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6635\"></p>\n'),(6636,'<p>1228</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6637\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-2.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6638\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6639\"></p>\n\n<p>200</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6640\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6641\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-6.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6642\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-7.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6643\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<p>1265</p>\n'),(6644,'<p>On December 28th, ShanghaiTech University laid its foundation in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), which marks substantial progress has been made in the preparatory work for establishing the university.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-1_TP3DDqk.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1_TP3DDqk.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6645\"></p>\n\n<p>Ms. Yicui YinDeputy Secretary of the Shanghai CPC Committee, Prof. Erwei Shi, Vice President of CAS, Prof. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, along with Mr. Lin Xu, Secretary of Pudong New District CPC Committee, Mr. Xuebing Zhang and Mr. Xiaoming Shen, Vice Mayors of Shanghai Municipal Government, visited the laboratories of ShanghaiTech University and investigated the campus master plan.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-2_Jyy3iPK.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2_Jyy3iPK.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6646\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-3_Ej0Yt4b.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3_Ej0Yt4b.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6647\"></p>\n\n<p>Around 200 professors of ShanghaiTech University, leaders from departments of Shanghai Municipal Government and Pudong New Area Government, representatives from other universities in Shanghai, principals of CAS Shanghai Branch and institutes as well as delegates from partners involved in campus design and construction witnessed the launch of campus construction project altogether.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-4_JnheOOm.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4_JnheOOm.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6648\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Bird\'s View</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-5_WgpppZb.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5_WgpppZb.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6649\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Library</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-6_e43iOqe.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6_e43iOqe.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6650\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Teaching Block</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-7_WiW6dLY.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7_WiW6dLY.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6651\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Arts and Venue Street</p>\n\n<p>Located at the center of Zhangjiang high-tech industrial development zone, ShanghaiTech integrates with Shanghai Advanced Research Institute (SARI) in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science and Technology Park, which covers approximately one square kilometer. At the established Multidisciplinary Frontier Research Base in Pudong S&amp;T Park of CAS, room has been reserved for universitys laboratories, classrooms and offices. The laboratories have been initiated in advance.</p>\n'),(6652,'<p>2013511</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-1.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6653\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-2.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6654\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6655\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6656\"></p>\n'),(6657,'<p>On May 11th, the ceremony marking the beginning of construction of ShanghaiTech University was held in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-1_9KewrJE.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1_9KewrJE.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6658\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-2_CGoidJ1.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2_CGoidJ1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6659\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-3_xDiEWpn.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3_xDiEWpn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6660\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-4_K7R5wn1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4_K7R5wn1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6661\"></p>\n'),(6662,'<p>On the morning of July 8th, ShanghaiTech 2013 summer camp for undergraduates formally kicked off in YueYang Road campus with 212 participants from 123 universities all over the country. Professor Mianheng Jiang, Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and President of Shanghai Branch, Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), handed the Camp flag over to the student representative on behalf of ShanghaiTech and initiated the camp. Professor Jie Yin, Vice Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Deputy Director of Shanghai Education Commission, Professor Jinkang Gong, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, as well as leaders of ShanghaiTech schools and institutes attended the opening ceremony.<br>\n<br>\nProfessor Mianheng Jiang delivered a speech named Realizing China Dream through Innovation and Entrepreneurship. He elaborated on the founding idea and mission of ShanghaiTech combined with national development strategy and social needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-1_uW6jad6.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_uW6jad6.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6663\"></p>\n\n<p>Professor Jie Yin outlined the preparation progress of ShanghaiTech University. ShanghaiTech University is characterized as a small-scale, high-level research university. It will tightly integrate education with innovative research and entrepreneurship to meet national and local development needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-2_UuzZRDW.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_UuzZRDW.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6664\"><br>\nProfessor Jinkang Gong explained in detail the training program of ShanghaiTech for graduate students, which ensures the implementation of the founding idea and the mission of ShanghaiTech.<br>\n<img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-3_psrEDRF.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_psrEDRF.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6665\"><br>\nIn the end of the ceremony, an overview of School of Physical Science and Technology (SPST), School of Information Science and Technology (SIST), School of Life Science and Technology (SLST), as well as School of Entrepreneurship and Management (SEM) was presented.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-4_eJbJPnn.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4_eJbJPnn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6666\"></p>\n\n<p>This was the 2nd Summer Camp held by ShanghaiTech University. Three schools respectively arranged a variety of activities for students according to their different subject characteristics. Participants of SPST will enter into different institutes of CAS Shanghai Branch, getting involved in group research, and students of SIST will compete in groups learning how to solve practical problems with classroom knowledge, while students of SLST will have the chance to join seminars where excellent reports will be presented by academicians and renowned scholars.</p>\n'),(6667,'<p>782013  123212  </p>\n\n<p>+</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-1_Qf1Adfm.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_Qf1Adfm.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6668\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-2_pY2mH8R.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_pY2mH8R.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6669\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-3_NnkqS10.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_NnkqS10.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6670\"></p>\n\n<p>iHuman</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6671\"></p>\n\n<p>   </p>\n'),(6672,'<p>89111022154 </p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-1.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6673\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-2.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6674\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-3.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6675\"></p>\n\n<p>   </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-4.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-4.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6676\"></p>\n'),(6677,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6678,'<p>93296 12 </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6679\"></p>\n\n<p>   </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-2.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6680\"></p>\n\n<p>  3D </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6681\"></p>\n\n<p>HyperloopElon Musk </p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6682\"></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6683\"></p>\n\n<p>iHumanRaymond C. Stevens </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-6.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6684\"></p>\n\n<p>  </p>\n\n<p>2013</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-7.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6685\"></p>\n'),(6686,'<p>ShanghaiTechs first batch of 296 graduate students started their first day of 2013 semester on September 3rd. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-1_SsCQCix.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1_SsCQCix.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6687\"></p>\n\n<p>The ceremony was organized in a novel and human-oriented format to match this brand new university. In front of the slideshow of the self-introduction of each student, the dean of each school announced the names of their students one by one. Madam Tiehui Weng, Deputy Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and Vice Mayor of Shanghai, granted each of the 3 student representatives an experiment record notebook and a crystal key as symbols of fact-finding spirit and pursuit of knowledge. What impressed the participants most was the exalting speech from Prof.Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-2_yUa0O3U.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2_yUa0O3U.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6688\"><br>\nCentering around Jinping Xis Chinese Dream, Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-3_M242EmH.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3_M242EmH.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6689\"></p>\n\n<p>Jiang encouraged the students to learn from Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who made Space X and Tesla the electrical car, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop the super high-speed train), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Jiang also mentioned the Chinese mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the bounded gaps conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-4_wPNOKe3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4_wPNOKe3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6690\"></p>\n\n<p>As professor representatives, Xi Wang(Academician, Director of Shanghai Institute of Microsystem and Information Technology) and Raymond Stevens (Director of iHuman Institute of ShanghaiTech) reflected on their academic experience, expressed their excitement to join ShanghaiTech and encouraged the students to seize the day.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-5_P6ts1Zd.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5_P6ts1Zd.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6691\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-6_Tke5VH9.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6_Tke5VH9.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6692\"></p>\n\n<p>Mingchao Jiang, a student from School of Physical Science and Technology, gave the speech on behalf of the new students and talked about his understanding on innovation and human-centeredness.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-7_dtF30kv.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7_dtF30kv.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6693\"></p>\n\n<p>At the end of the ceremony,Mianheng Jiang officially announced the opening of the semester. After the ceremony students had an interaction session with professors.</p>\n'),(6694,'<p><span><span style=\"\"><span>296 young graduate students began their exciting ShanghaiTech career on September 3</span><sup><span>rd</span></sup><span>, 2013. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>The ceremony adopted non-traditional format to match this brand new university. Accompanied by slideshows, each school introduced their students one by one. Vice Major Tiehui Weng, Deputy Chief of the ShanghaiTech Preparation Work-Group, presented a lab notebook and a crystal key as symbols of truth searching spirit and pursuit of knowledge. As a highlight of the event, participants were treated by an exalting speech from Prof. Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Centering around the theme of Chinese Dream, Dr. Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Dr. Jiang encouraged the students to learn from individuals like Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who started Space X and Tesla, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Dr. Jiang also mentioned the example of a previously obscure mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the bounded gaps conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6695\"></span></span></p>\n'),(6696,'<p>Two officers of the National Natural Science Foundation fo China, Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on September 28th.</p>\n\n<p>They received warm welcome by SIST faculty professors. Prof. Zhi Ding, Prof. Shuguang Cui and Prof. Pingqiang Zhou met Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, introduced our university and school, and had a constructive talk with them.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402171045278532_boPUFVB.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532_boPUFVB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6697\"></p>\n'),(6698,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402171045278532.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6699\"></p>\n\n<p>928</p>\n'),(6700,'<p><span><span><span>A Contest named <em>Young Idea Award </em>was successfully held on November 10</span><sup><span>th</span></sup><span>, which was sponsored by SIST and received kind support from the office of Financial Services and the School of Entrepreneurship and Management at ShanghaiTech.<em> Young Idea Award </em>was designed for encouraging graduate students who have different and innovative understanding on scientific research or entrepreneurship. All the students from ShanghaiTech University were welcomed to join in the contest.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6702\"></p>\n\n<p><span>Over 20 students in eight teams took part in the contest. The topic named Creative Campus, which was designed by Yuying Bao, Xiangyu Jia, Ziran Xing from SIST, finally won the first prize.</span></p>\n\n<p><span><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6701\"></span></p>\n'),(6703,'<p>1010Young Idea AwardYoung Idea Award</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6705\"></p>\n\n<p>2083</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6704\"></p>\n'),(6706,'<p>102930</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6707\"></p>\n'),(6708,'<p><span><span>On behalf of the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, </span><span><span>Prof. Zhi Ding and Prof. Shuguang Cui took part in</span></span><span><span> the Future (5G) ICT Summit &amp; 5G Mobile and Communication Technologies Workshop, which was Hosted by FuTURE FORUM, co-organized by METIS Project and China Mobile and held in Beijing during Oct 29th</span><span>  Oct 30th</span><span>. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5_fZwIZWL.jpg\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5_fZwIZWL.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6709\"></p>\n'),(6710,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6711\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6712\"></p>\n\n<p>118Stephen Boyd100Stephen BoydStephen Boyd</p>\n'),(6713,'<p>Prof. Stephen Boyd, Samsung Professor of Engineering, and a Professor of Electrical Engineering at Stanford University, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on November 8<sup>th</sup>and presented an exciting seminar on Convex Optimization: From Real-Time Embedded to Large-Scale Distributed. Over 100 graduated students and faculty members from ShanghaiTech, Southeast University and Shanghai University, enjoyed the high-quality seminar, which stimulated many productive discussions.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6714\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Boydstalk focused on two extremes: real-time embedded convex optimization, and distributed convex optimization. For the first one, code generation can be used to generate extremely efficient and reliable solvers for small problems, which can execute in milliseconds or microseconds, and are ideal for embedding in real-time systems. At the other extreme, Prof. Boyed described methods for large-scale distributed optimization, which coordinate many solvers to solve large problems. Prof. Boyds talk is open, humorous, informative, and inspiring. The large crowd at the seminar includes faculty members from as for as Nanjing. In addition, the Audience was also treated with someaspiring insightsonhow to conduct high-quality research and how to become a real scholar.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6715\"></p>\n'),(6716,'<p>20131228</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>201420132014</p>\n\n<p>2014</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201403061346428421.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201403061346428421.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6717\"></p>\n'),(6718,'<p>The first meeting of the University Board of Trustees was held on December 28th 2013. The attending members are:</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Xu Kuangdi</strong></em>, Vice Chairman of 10th CPPCC National Committee; former Mayor of Shanghai, former President of the Chinese Academy of Engineering; Chairman of the University Council of the University<br>\n<em><strong>Zhou Xiaochuan</strong></em>, Vice Chairman of 12th CPPCC National Committee; Governor of the People\'s Bank of China.<br>\n<em><strong>Weng Tiehui</strong></em><strong>,</strong>Vice Mayor of Shanghai; Deputy Head of the Working Group of ShanghaiTech.<br>\n<em><strong>Ding Zhongli</strong></em>, Vice President of Chinese Academy of Sciences; Director of the Education Committee of CAS.<br>\n<em><strong>Fu Chengyu</strong></em><strong>,</strong>Chairman of China Petroleum &amp; Chemical Corporation.<br>\n<em><strong>Jiang Mianheng</strong></em><strong>,</strong>President of Chinese Academy of Sciences Shanghai Branch; Chairman of the Executive Committee of Shanghaitech.<br>\n<em><strong>Zhu Zhiyuan</strong></em><strong>,</strong>Executive Vice President of Chinese Academy of Sciences Shanghai Branch.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting was chaired by Xu Kuangdi.</p>\n\n<p>According to the By Laws of ShanghaiTech University approved by both CAS and Shanghai Municipality, the University Board of Trustees is the decision-making body of ShanghaiTech. It is composed of representatives from Shanghai Municipality, CAS, the university as well as expert from the industry. Its responsibilities include compiling and revising the By Laws, drafting the development strategy and plan; nominating the university President, appointing the administrative heads based on the President\'s nomination, reviewing the annual report, budget and final account, deciding the key issues of the university and etc,.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting reviewed the vision and goals of the university, the current status of teaching, research, recruitment, the campus construction and annual report 2014. The meeting approved the University Board of Trustees Rules of Procedure, key position appointment, as well as the final accounts of 2013 and budget for 2014.</p>\n\n<p>The University Board of Trustees pointed out that ShanghaiTech University has made considerable progress by reforming the university structure, management, nurturing of talents, human resource system and allocation of funding and has actively explored the deep integration of education, research and innovation. The members are confident that under the support of Ministry of Education, Shanghai Municipality, and the hard work of the all faculty and staff, ShanghaiTech will make new achievements in 2014.<img alt=\"Picture - 201403061346428421_z38VaAJ.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201403061346428421_z38VaAJ.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6719\"></p>\n'),(6720,'<p>20143</p>\n\n<p>1995199720002000200620062011200920141999ICCVDavid Marr2004NSFCAREER Award2005Young Investigator Award2011Gold Star Award2013IEEE Fellow2007-2011IEEE Trans. on Pattern Analysis and Machine IntelligenceIEEE Trans. on Information TheoryInternational Journal of Computer VisionIMA Journal on Information and InferenceSIAM Journal on Imaging SciencesICCV</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201405161418534052.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201405161418534052.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6721\"></p>\n'),(6722,'<p>Dr. Yi Ma, a famous scholar in computer vision, joined in the School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech University as a full-time professor who would lead the study of computer vision in March, 2014.</p>\n\n<p>Yi Ma received Bachelors degree in Automation and Applied Mathematics from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China, in 1995. He received a Master degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences (EECS) in 1997, a second Master degree in Mathematics in 2000, and the Ph.D. degree in EECS in 2000, all from the University of California at Berkeley. He served as associated professor from 2000 to 2006 and vice professor from 2006 to 2011 of the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. From 2009 to 2014, he served as research manager for the Visual Computing Group at Microsoft Research Asia, Beijing, China. His PhD research won the David Marr Best Paper Award at the International Conference on Computer Vision (ICCV) in 1999. He was the recipient of the Faculty Early Career Development (CAREER) Award from the National Science Foundation (NSF) in 2004. He was also the recipient of the Young Investigator Program (YIP) Award from the Office of Naval Research (ONR) in 2005. He received the Gold Star Award from Microsoft Corporate in 2009. He has served as an associate editor of the IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence (TPAMI) from 2007 to 2011. He became a Fellow of IEEE in 2013. He has served as an associate editor of the IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence (TPAMI). He currently serves as the associate editors for the IEEE Transactions on Information Theory, the International Journal of Computer Vision (IJCV), the IMA Journal on Information and Inference, and the SIAM Journal on Imaging Sciences. He also served as the Area Chair, the Program Chair and the General Chair for ICCV and was invited to present reports in many international conferences.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201405161418534052_S31shdt.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201405161418534052_S31shdt.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6723\"></p>\n'),(6724,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201408191139291671.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201408191139291671.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6725\"></p>\n\n<p>(Thomas Reuters)20146(Highly Cited Researchers 2014http://highlycited.com)Web of Science1%212002-20123215The worlds most influential scientific minds.</p>\n\n<p>Dr. Cui19972000McMaster2005Texas A&amp;MDr. Cui)Dr. CuiIEEE2012,(IEEE TSP, TWC, TVT, CL)IEEE(WTC)IEEESPCOMDr. Cui2013IEEE Fellow8IEEE2014IEEE Transactions on Big DataSteering Committee</p>\n'),(6726,'<p>20149587,99</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974.jpg\" title=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6727\"></p>\n'),(6728,'<p>The faculty and staff of SIST joyfully welcome our new students coming in 2014, which include the first batch of undergraduate students and second batch of graduate students. Through substantial activities in the orientation, students got to know more about ShanghaiTech and strengthened their confidence towards future study and living here. The graduate courses have started since September 9. Undergraduate freshmen are going to set out for their long expected college education very soon after finishing their military training.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974_c84HgXy.jpg\" title=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974_c84HgXy.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6729\"></p>\n'),(6730,'<p></p>\n'),(6731,'<p>Prof. Jinyi Yu, Associate Professor at the University of Delaware, and Prof. Xin Li, Associate Professor at Carnegie Mellon University have joined the SIST as visiting professors.</p>\n'),(6732,'<p>20147Soeren SchwertfegerBoris Houska2015</p>\n'),(6733,'<p>The professors who have joined the SIST since July 2014 includes: Dr. Yanling Geng, Xiaojun Yuan, Shenghua Gao, Soeren Schwertfeger, Haoyu Wang, and Boris Houska as Assistant Professors, and Xiliang Luo as Associate Professor. In addition, 6 new colleagues include Dr. Xiaopei Liu, Dr. Jie Lu, Dr. Ziyang Meng, Dr. Xiong Wang, Dr. Liangfeng Zhang, Dr. Youyi Zheng will report on duty later in 2015.</p>\n'),(6734,'<p>2015122</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004245165.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004245165.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6735\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004506755.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004506755.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6736\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310005041729.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310005041729.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6737\"></p>\n'),(6738,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) has held their first retreat meeting in the Puxi campus at Jan. 22, 2015. All presidents of ShanghaiTech including President Mianheng Jiang, and some colleagues in other functional offices has also attended this meeting. In the meeting, Prof. Zhi Ding, the executive dean reviewed the faculty recruitment and development since establishing and summarized the guiding comments from the international advisory board. After that, the chairs of Academic Committee, Curriculum Committee, Graduate Admission Committee, Seminar Committee, and Public Relation Committee reported their achievements in 2014, introduced their drafted by-laws, and discussed their future plan. After the reports, the faculty members of SIST make an extensive communication with the university leaders regarding different issues about the school development; they have also made a brainstorm about their future roadmap.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004245165_hgmDMnB.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004245165_hgmDMnB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6739\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004506755_syJmdXe.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004506755_syJmdXe.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6740\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310005041729_ZwroWNi.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310005041729_ZwroWNi.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6741\"></p>\n'),(6742,'<p>2015</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201502031733531115.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201502031733531115.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6743\"></p>\n'),(6744,'<p>Supported by the Berkeley-ShanghaiTech-Exchange (BeSTEC) Program, the first delegation of SIST@ShanghaiTech, consisting of Professor Pingqiang Zhou, Professor Shenghua Gao, and Mr. Kai Liao (2nd year graduate student), has started their Berkeley time from the last week of Jan. 2015.</p>\n\n<p>According to the program, professors and students of SIST can attend part of the Berkeley courses, which would later be offered to SIST students. This program will also help the junior faculty members at ShanghaiTech to build research connections with the faculty at Berkeley.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201502031733531115_7F2rgXp.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201502031733531115_7F2rgXp.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6745\"></p>\n'),(6746,'<p>DAC (Design Automation Conference) 2015A Statistical Methodology for Noise Sensor Placement and Full-Chip Voltage Map Generation</p>\n\n<p>DACDAC6</p>\n'),(6747,'<p>SIST student Xiaochen Lius paper was accepted by Design Automation Conference (DAC) 2015. His paper is titled A Statistical Methodology for Noise Sensor Placement and Full-Chip Voltage Map Generation. Xiaochens advisor is Prof. Pingqiang Zhou.</p>\n\n<p>DAC is the premier conference for the design and automation of electronic systems. DAC 2015 will be held in San Francisco in June 2015.</p>\n'),(6748,'<p>2015420Leonidas GuibasNetworks of Shapes and Images</p>\n\n<p>Leonidas GuibasGuibasACM FellowIEEE Fellow, ACM Allen NewellVoronoi-DelaunayEMDKineticKDSMetropolis light transportheat-kernel signaturesfunctional maps</p>\n\n<p>GuibasGuibas</p>\n\n<p>Leonidas Guibas </p>\n\n<p> Leonidas Guibas 1976Donald KnuthXerox PARCDECDEC SRC1984John HershbergerJack SnoeyinkJorge Stolfi,  David SalesinEric Veach Niloy Mitra</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201504232315256998.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 201504232315256998.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6749\"></p>\n'),(6750,'<p>On April 20, 2015, Leonidas Guibas, professor of computer science at Stanford University, gave a talk named Networks of Shapes and Images to ShanghaiTech faculty and students.</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Yi Ma, executive dean of School of Information Science and Technology (SIST), introduced the speakers academic career. As an ACM Fellow, an IEEE Fellow and winner of the ACM Allen Newell Award, Prof. Guibas is a well-known master in computer graphics. Some of his well-known accomplishments include the analysis of double hashing, red-black trees, the quad-edge data structure, Voronoi-Delaunay algorithms, the Earth Movers distance, Kinetic Data Structures (KDS), Metropolis light transport, heat-kernel signatures and functional maps.</p>\n\n<p>Prof. Guibas pointed out that, across science, engineering, medicine and business we faced a deluge of data coming from sensors, simulations or activities of individuals on the internet, and the data often contain geometric and/or visual characters. Furthermore, the geometric data sets we collected were frequently highly correlated, reflecting information about the same or similar entities, or echoing semantically important repetitions/symmetries or hierarchical structures common to both man-made and natural objects. He described general mathematical and computational tools for the construction, analysis and exploitation of such relational networks. By creating societies of data sets and their associations in a globally consistent way, we enabled a certain joint understanding of the data that provided the powers of abstraction, analogy, compression, error correction and summarization. Faculty and students were greatly attracted to the intriguing images Prof. Guibas showed during the talk, and had extensive discussion with him afterwards.</p>\n\n<p>Bio:</p>\n\n<p>Leonidas Guibas obtained his Ph.D. from Stanford in 1976, under the supervision of Donald Knuth. His subsequent employers include Xerox PARC, MIT, and DEC/SRC. He has been at Stanford since 1984 as Professor of Computer Science. He has produced several Ph.D. students who are well-known in computational geometry, such as John Hershberger, Jack Snoeyink and Jorge Stolfi, or in computer graphics, such as David Salesin, Eric Veach and Niloy Mitra.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201504232315256998_OMLDqoo.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 201504232315256998_OMLDqoo.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6751\"></p>\n'),(6752,'<p>2015/()2.5MW / 4MW</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201505200733119750.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201505200733119750.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6753\"></p>\n'),(6754,'<p><i>Renewable Energy System</i>is a new graduate course offered in the fall semester of 2015. As a supplement to this course, the school has organized a field trip to a local sino-foreign wind power company, Shanghai Electric Wind Energy Co. Ltd / Siemens Wind Power Turbines (Shanghai) Co., Ltd. Thanks to the guidance of Yi Zhang, an engineer of the company, the visitors have listened to the state of the art of wind power industry in China, as well as the history of the company. After the introduction, they were guided to visit the assembly workshop of 2.5 MW / 4 MW wind turbines. Finally, they have a close look at the testing wind farm on the shore of East China Sea. The field trip has offered the students an immediate and memorable impression on renewable energy system and local wind power industry.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201505200733119750_1PUK7EL.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201505200733119750_1PUK7EL.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6755\"></p>\n'),(6756,'<p>5263D</p>\n\n<p>3D3D3D3D</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20150609133045145.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20150609133045145.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6757\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331003762.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331003762.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6758\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331137173.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331137173.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6759\"></p>\n'),(6769,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6770,'<p>On May 26th, Deputy director of Shanghai Museum Dr. Hu Jiang and President Jiang Mianheng, accompanied by Professor Ma Yi, executive dean of SIST, visited the 3D Imaging Lab housed at SIST.</p>\n\n<p>Prof. Yu Jingyi demonstrated a novel 3D imaging system to the visitors and gave an in-depth presentation on its acquisition, data transmission and display modules. Of particular interest is the portable camera array that enables naked-eye 3D viewing. All visitors were impressed by the demonstration. After that, the two parties have further discussed potential collaborations on applying the 3D imaging system for a broad range of applications at Shanghai Museum. President Jiang Mianheng pointed out that, integrating research and real-life application is central to the mission of ShanghaiTech and SIST. He hopes that discussions today will lead to concrete collaboration between ShanghaiTech and Shanghai Museum in the near future.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20150609133045145_qMff62E.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20150609133045145_qMff62E.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6771\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331003762_2ZwmfSB.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331003762_2ZwmfSB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6772\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331137173_P1lWPJ6.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331137173_P1lWPJ6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6773\"></p>\n'),(6782,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6783,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6784,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6788,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - Examining the Landscape and Impact of Android Application Plagiarism.jpg\" title=\"Picture - Examining the Landscape and Impact of Android Application Plagiarism.jpg\" src=\"/static/